# Qube ‚Äî Cursor project index

**Canonical rules and long-form directives:** `.clinerules` (source of truth).

**Domain rules (Cursor `.mdc`):** `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` ‚Äî e.g. `native_engine.mdc` (dual-engine inference, execution policy, prompt template router, template_override + model_override_store self-heal, reasoning detection, debug stack), `tools-diagnostics.mdc` (CLI: `run_ablation`, `view_llm_logs`, `llm_prompt_diff`; ablation may persist `~/.qube/model_overrides.json`), `ui-rules.mdc` (Think toggle / telemetry polling).

**Native LLM inference debug (internal engine only, observer-only):** All optional; no prompt/sampling/stream changes. Logger: **`Qube.NativeLLM.Debug`**. Typical order after each completion: (1) **`QUBE_LLM_TOKEN_TRACE`** ‚Äî live vs post-hoc vs sampler GT (`native_token_trace`, `native_sampler_gt`); (2) **`QUBE_LLM_CAUSALITY`** ‚Äî `llm_execution_causality_report` (`llm_execution_causality`); (3) **`QUBE_LLM_COUNTERFACTUAL`** ‚Äî analytical `llm_counterfactual_simulation` (`llm_counterfactual`). Baseline / parity: **`QUBE_LLM_DEBUG`** / **`QUBE_LLM_PROMPT_VALIDATE`** + **`QUBE_LLM_REFERENCE_JSON`** (optional `first_sampler_token_ids` for first-token diff). **Model reasoning profile (metadata only):** `core/model_reasoning_profile.py` classifies thinking-token support (**`detect_model_reasoning_profile`**: tokenizer scan with first-hit exit, GGUF **`tokenizer.chat_template`**, weak **`metadata_template`** hints, name/path heuristics; **`_llama_cpp_model`** = **`_model`** or **`model`**) + profile **`ExecutionMode`** (`direct` / `thinking` / `hybrid` / `unknown`); **`NativeLlamaEngine`** stores **`_execution_mode`** after load. **Think toggle sync:** **`main.py`** wires **`native_llama_engine.load_finished` ‚Üí `ConversationsView.refresh_think_toggle`**; **`ConversationsView.showEvent`** re-syncs when returning to the screen. **Central execution policy:** `core/execution_policy.py` defines **`ExecutionPolicy`** via **`resolve_execution_policy(...)`** ‚Äî profile + QSettings Think + **`engine_mode`**; telemetry **`ui_display_thinking`**; **`LLMWorker`** stream filters follow **`strip_thinking_output`**. **Prompt construction (observability bundle):** `core/prompt_template_router.py` ‚Äî **`infer_template_type`** (chatml / llama3 / phi / mistral / jinja / fallback from **`tokenizer.chat_template`** + **`chat_format`**); **`apply_reasoning_injection`** (model-aware **`reasoning_mode`** text ‚Äî no generic overlay); **`build_prompt_bundle`** = **`reconstruct_formatted_prompt`** + injection + merged stops, then **Phase 4** **`core/template_override.py`** (**`detect_template_override`**: model-name stops + assistant anchor; **`[LLM-TEMPLATE-OVERRIDE]`**), then **Phase 5** **`core/model_override_store.py`** (**`get_override`**: persisted **`LearnedOverride`** from ablation self-heal ‚Äî merge **`extra_stop_tokens`** + anchor; **`[LLM-SELF-HEAL-APPLY]`**; policy fields in JSON are not applied in the router); logs **`[LLM-TEMPLATE]`** + **`[LLM-PROMPT-ROUTER]`** on **`Qube.PromptTemplateRouter`**; **`NativeLlamaEngine._prepare_validation_and_logs`** uses the bundle for validation / logs (**`create_chat_completion(messages=...)`** unchanged). **Load-time behavior profiling (internal):** `core/model_behavior.py` ‚Äî ablation on model load (skipped when **`get_override(model_name)`** already has a persisted self-heal entry ‚Äî **`[LLM-SELF-HEAL] skip ablation`**) ‚Üí **`classify_model_behavior`** / **`resolve_behavior_override`** ‚Üí **`get_execution_policy()`** may adjust execution fields; JSON **`llm_model_behavior_profile`** on **`Qube.NativeLLM.Debug`**. **Self-heal learning:** `core/prompt_ablation_harness.py` **`infer_override_from_ablation`** + **`store_override`** ‚Üí **`~/.qube/model_overrides.json`**; **`[LLM-SELF-HEAL]`** when a new override is written. **Diagnostic-only:** `core/prompt_ablation_harness.py` + **`python -m tools.run_ablation`** ‚Äî **`AblationReport`** (not per-request). Logs **`[LLM-DEBUG] execution_policy=...`**, **`[LLM-ABLATION] ...`**. See `.cursor/rules/native_engine.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/tools-diagnostics.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/ui-rules.mdc`.

Below is the **Section 3 directory treemap** (keep in sync with `.clinerules` Section 3 when you add files).

```text
Qube/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ main.py                 # Entry point: NativeLlamaEngine, LLMWorker, MainWindow; load_finished ‚Üí conversations Think refresh (refresh_think_toggle).
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ assets/                 # Static UI and Brand Assets (Immutable)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ fonts /             # Custom Inter font families.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ icons/              # App icons, window logos, UI element SVGs.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ sounds/             # (Optional) Notification chimes or UI sound effects.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ styles/             # base.qss (dark), light.qss ‚Äî includes #SettingsMenuButton and :disabled states for locked Prestige dropdowns.
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ screenshots/        # Screenshots of the app for Github
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ui/                     # Presentation Layer (Dumb Components)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ main_window.py      # Frameless shell, nav, global toolbar (incl. LOCAL LLM SettingsMenuButton + Prestige menus), top bar, theme toggle; passes native_engine into TelemetryView for read-only capability telemetry.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/         # Reusable custom UI components.
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ memory_debug.py # Live UI debug panel exposing internal ranking math (semantic distance, confidence, strength, and final score) of the memory retrieval pipeline
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ source_viewer.py # UI dialog component for displaying the raw text of cited RAG documents and web sources
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ  toggle.py       # Toggle (custom design) we use in the UI    
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ views/              # isolated widget files for each major screen
‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ __init__.py     
‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ conversations_view.py # PrestigeDialog, chat stages, Think toggle (telemetry ui_display_thinking; refresh_think_toggle on load_finished via main + showEvent).
‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ library_view.py # Knowledge base screen
‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ settings_view.py # Settings: dual-engine (engine vs external provider), GPU offload + CPU thread pool QSliders (caps from gpu_layers_cap / cpu_threads), ~75% hardware defaults on first run (missing QSettings keys), local GGUF list + Use/Delete, PrestigeDialog only (no QMessageBox).
‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ router_dashboard.py # Visualizations go into the Telemetry screen
‚îÇ       ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ telemetry_view.py # Telemetry screen (hardware graphs, router metrics, optional LLM debug panel); ‚ÄúNative LLM ‚Äî Model capability‚Äù card polls NativeLlamaEngine.get_model_reasoning_telemetry() when internal engine is wired.
‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ model_manager_view.py # App Store-style Hub browser (search, README, quant dropdown), local GGUF library, and download/cancel flow with disk guardrails for the native engine.
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ core/                   # System, Hardware, Preferences, Network, and Native LLM helpers (28 files; alphabetical)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ app_settings.py     # QSettings: engine mode, internal GGUF path, internal_n_gpu_layers (VRAM cap + optional 75% default), internal_n_threads (logical CPU cap + optional 75% default), llm_models_dir, chat format token, etc.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ audio_utils.py      # PyAudio device discovery and index mapping.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ cpu_threads.py      # Logical CPU count (psutil/os), max_cpu_threads_for_ui, default_internal_n_threads (~75% of cores) for native llama.cpp n_threads.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ database.py         # SQLite session/document API for the UI.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ execution_policy.py # Central ExecutionPolicy + resolve_execution_policy (model profile + user Think override + engine_mode); reasoning allowance, UI/TTS strip flags, enforcement soft/hard (no prompt/sampling changes).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ gpu_layers_cap.py   # VRAM detection + max_safe_n_gpu_layers + default_internal_n_gpu_layers_suggested (~75% of cap) for first-run GPU slider default.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ gpu_monitor.py      # GPUMonitor: NVIDIA (pynvml) / Linux sysfs / Windows perf for load % telemetry (not VRAM caps).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ llm_counterfactual.py # QUBE_LLM_COUNTERFACTUAL: analytical what-if scenarios (no inference) ‚Äî one intervention at a time; emits llm_counterfactual_simulation.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ llm_debug_sink.py   # Rotating file handler for Qube.NativeLLM.Debug -> logs/llm_debug.log (terminal quiet via logging_bootstrap).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ llm_execution_causality.py # QUBE_LLM_CAUSALITY: post-inference causal report (prompt/template/stops/sampler vs live); optional LM Studio first-token diff via reference JSON.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ logging_bootstrap.py # init_llm_debug_logging(): attach LLM debug file sink; keep stdout clean.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ model_behavior.py # classify_model_behavior + resolve_behavior_override; load-time ablation ‚Üí execution overrides (no prompt/sampling in resolver).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ model_override_store.py # Phase 5: ~/.qube/model_overrides.json ‚Äî LearnedOverride load/save; build_prompt_bundle merges extra_stop_tokens + assistant anchor; [LLM-SELF-HEAL-APPLY].
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ model_reasoning_profile.py # detect_model_reasoning_profile: tokenizer scan (first hit) + chat_template + metadata_template weak hints + name/path; _llama_cpp_model; ModelReasoningProfile + ExecutionMode; metadata only ‚Äî no prompt/sampling changes.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ native_llama_chat.py # OpenAI-style message normalization + GGUF chat_template / chat_format alignment for native create_chat_completion.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ native_llama_inference.py # Extra stop strings + kwargs for native create_chat_completion (merged with formatter stops; LM Studio‚Äìstyle guards).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ native_llm_debug.py # QUBE_LLM_DEBUG: reconstructed prompt logging, stop merge helpers, EOS/BOS, inference request JSON logs (LM Studio parity tooling).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ native_meta_leading_strip.py # Native streaming path: optional strip of brief meta-instruction openers at start of assistant text (conservative).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ native_sampler_gt.py  # Sampler ground truth: wraps Llama.generate during inference; prompt-token assembly mirrors llama-cpp-python _create_completion.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ native_token_trace.py # QUBE_LLM_TOKEN_TRACE: JSON logs ‚Äî live delta re-tokenization, post-hoc, vs sampler ground truth (see native_sampler_gt).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ network.py          # Port scanning (Ollama/LM Studio detection).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ prompt_ablation_harness.py # NON-PRODUCTION: diagnostic ablation scenarios (prompt/stop variants, leakage heuristics, AblationReport); run_ablation_test uses create_completion(prompt=...) ‚Äî not the app chat path; infer_override_from_ablation + store_override ‚Üí ~/.qube/model_overrides.json; [LLM-SELF-HEAL].
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ prompt_integrity_validator.py # Prompt structure checks, LM Studio parity scoring, QUBE_LLM_REFERENCE_JSON / first_sampler_token_ids (validation only); attaches model_reasoning_profile_detected + execution_mode (resolved policy mode) to validation JSON (metadata).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ prompt_template_router.py # infer_template_type + apply_reasoning_injection + build_prompt_bundle; template_override + model_override_store layers; [LLM-TEMPLATE] / [LLM-TEMPLATE-OVERRIDE] / [LLM-SELF-HEAL-APPLY] / [LLM-PROMPT-ROUTER]; validation/log prefetch (chat path unchanged).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ redacted_thinking_filter.py # Stream filter for <redacted_thinking> blocks (DeepSeek-R1‚Äìstyle; internal engine path).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ richtext_styles.py  # App-wide link palette / rich text helpers.
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ template_override.py # Phase 4: detect_template_override (phi / Nemotron / Mistral name heuristics) ‚Äî extra stops + assistant anchor in build_prompt_bundle only; [LLM-TEMPLATE-OVERRIDE].
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ workers/                # Background Event Loops (QThreads)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ audio_worker.py     # Captures audio, runs OpenWakeWord.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ stt_worker.py       # Runs Faster-Whisper on audio byte chunks.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ llm_worker.py       # Streams LLM tokens, RAG cascade; internal native path uses NativeLlamaEngine.get_execution_policy() for thinking strip/display (policy-driven stream filters).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ native_llama_engine.py # QThread: Llama load/unload/generate; load-time behavior ablation (skipped if get_override has persisted self-heal) + model_behavior overrides; build_prompt_bundle in _prepare_validation_and_logs; detect_model_reasoning_profile; get_execution_policy(); [LLM-DEBUG] reasoning_profile + execution_policy + llm_model_behavior_profile; post-inference: token trace ‚Üí causality ‚Üí counterfactual (env-gated).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ hf_model_search_worker.py # Background Hugging Face Hub model search (GGUF-oriented filtering) for the Model Manager browse list.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ hf_readme_worker.py # Fetches repository README markdown from Hugging Face for the Model Manager detail pane.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ hf_repo_files_worker.py # Lists .gguf file paths in a model repo via Hub API for quantization selection.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ model_download_worker.py # Streams GGUF downloads from Hugging Face with Content-Length disk pre-check, cooperative cancel, and .part file cleanup.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ enrichment_worker.py # Constructs atomic memories that are then stored in LanceDB.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ tts_worker.py       # Manages universal TTS adapters (Piper/Kokoro) and audio queues.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ title_worker.py       # Generates titles for the conversations list (bundled Qwen 0.5B performs it)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ intent_router.py       # Uses semantic vector embeddings for intent routing instead of rigid keywords, while cognitive_router manages load and thresholds.
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ingestion_worker.py # Parses, chunks, and embeds documents in the background.
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ rag/                    # Retrieval-Augmented Generation Engine
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ embedder.py         # llama-cpp-python Vulkan engine with Nomic v1.5 GGUF.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ store.py            # LanceDB interface (Disk-native, zero-copy vector storage).
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ chunker.py          # Semantic text splitting (1500 chars / 150 overlap).
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ parsers.py          # Document parsers (PDF, EPUB, TXT, MD, Wiki dumps).
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ mcp/                    # Model Context Protocol Interfaces
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ rag_tool.py         # Disk-backed search function called by the LLM interceptor.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ internet_tool.py    # Web search functionality
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ memory_tool.py      # Retrieves stored facts using a hybrid scoring algorithm (semantic similarity + extracted confidence + reinforcement strength) with expanded candidate pooling to prevent starvation while strictly enforcing token budgets.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ router.py           # Maintained as a legacy fallback for the cognitive_router, this component provides stable, deterministic query routing using fixed cosine-similarity thresholds and hardcoded semantic anchors.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ cognitive_router.py # Manages adaptive query routing by dynamically adjusting retrieval thresholds based on real-time system latency, load penalties, and conversation intent drift.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ router_self_tuner.py # Acts as an autonomous feedback loop that continuously tunes cognitive routing sensitivities based on real-time telemetry (latency and hit rates) to penalize inefficient tool usage.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ router_telemetry.py # Maintains a lightweight, in-memory queue of recent routing events to track latency, hit rates, and route distributions for real-time performance monitoring.
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ models/                 # Local AI Weights (Organized by function)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ stt/                # Faster-Whisper weights.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ tts/                # Piper/Kokoro voices and configs.
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ embeddings/         # RAG embedding models (ONNX).
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ wakeword/           # OpenWakeWord detection models.
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ data/                   # LanceDB vector storage directory.
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ tools/                  # Utilities package (python -m tools.<module>): llm_prompt_diff.py, view_llm_logs.py, run_ablation.py (prompt ablation CLI ‚Äî diagnostic only).
```
